

	 
      this thanksgiving, i am most thankful for forgiveness. i believe that when you really do love someone, you are able to truly forgive and forget. that is the meaning of unconditional love, that no matter what has been said and done, you are able to overcome your hurt and anger and continue to love as before. to forgive is not just to say that you forgive. the real evidence is that you are able to overlook the transgression and permanently move past it. if you are unable to do so, it doesn't mean that you don't love the person, but it probably means you don't love him or her more than yourself. this is what my mom has taught me today. i am so thankful for her unconditional and selfless love.  happy thanksgiving everyone. 
     
    
